EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to periods of observance; designating the month
of July of each year as “Muslim American Heritage
Month” in this State; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, certain days, weeks and months of observance are
2 recognized in this State. (NRS 236.018-236.095) This bill designates the month of
3 July of each year as “Muslim American Heritage Month” in the State of Nevada
4 and requires the Governor to issue annually a proclamation encouraging the
5 observance of this month.
1 WHEREAS, The Muslim American community in Nevada can
2 trace its beginnings to the mid-20th century; and
3 WHEREAS, Masjid As-Sabur is the oldest mosque in Las Vegas,
4 Nevada and has served the local community since the 1970s; and
5 WHEREAS, The Northern Nevada Muslim Community was
6 established in 1980 to serve the community in and around Reno,
7 Nevada; and
8 WHEREAS, Muslim Americans have contributed to the society of
9 Nevada and the United States by making advancements in
10 architecture, arts, business, community, culture, government, law,
11 medicine, the military, religion and sports; and
